doc_prompt = (
        "Convert the following technical troubleshooting content into valid **Confluence Storage Format XHTML**, used in the Confluence REST API with `representation: storage`.\n\n"
        "Strict formatting rules to follow:\n"
        "1. **Headings:** Use <h2> for major sections, <h3> for subsections.\n"
        "2. **Lists:** Use nested <ul><li>...</li></ul> tags. Maintain indentation for sublists.\n"
        "3. **Bold Text:** Use <strong>text</strong> (not <b>).\n"
        "4. **Code Blocks:** Use the Confluence code macro, and ensure CDATA blocks contain only raw text:\n"
        "<ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\">\n"
        "  <ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">bash</ac:parameter>\n"
        "  <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[\n"
        "your code here\n"
        "  ]]></ac:plain-text-body>\n"
        "</ac:structured-macro>\n"
        "5. **Inline Code:** Use <code>inline_code</code> (not backticks).\n"
        "6. **Links:** Use <a href=\"URL\">text</a> format only.\n"
        "7. **XML Compliance:** Ensure well-formed XHTML:\n"
        "   - Close all tags properly.\n"
        "   - Escape all &, <, > except inside CDATA.\n"
        "   - Avoid placing macros inside lists or paragraphs.\n"
        "8. **Preserve All Technical Content:** Do not omit any detail or rewrite the original text.\n"
        "9. **Final Output:** Return only the converted XHTML, no markdown, YAML, explanations, or comments.\n\n"
        "Here is the input content:\n"
        "---\n"
        f"{doc_input}\n"
        "---"
    )
